article.headline: Eastern Kentucky 63, Samford 43
article.story: RICHMOND, Ky. (AP) -- Matt Witt scored 20 points to lead Eastern Kentucky to a 63-43 victory over Samford Thursday night. Witt finished 7-for-13, including 6-for-10 from 3-point range. Jon Bentley added 10 points and 10 rebounds for the Colonels (10-12, 5-6 Ohio Valley Conference). Tyson Dorsey led Samford (10-12, 5-6) with 10 points. Samford pulled to within 11 three times in the final 10 minutes but could get no closer as Eastern built a 59-39 lead with 1:45 left. Eastern shot a season-high 56.8 percent from the field (25-for-44) and limited the Bulldogs to 35 percent shooting (14-for-40). Witt missed his first five shots from the field, but hit a 3-pointer with nine seconds left in the first half to give the Colonels a 22-19 halftime lead. Witt, who had 17 of his points in the second half, connected on back-to-back shots from long range as Eastern went on an 11-3 run for a 33-22 lead with 16:44 remaining.
